```

This check ensures that if the system is in lockdown mode (`LOCKDOWN_DBG_WRITE_KERNEL`), the debugger will either switch to KDB mode (if available) or exit entirely. This is a direct mitigation against unauthorized access to kernel memory when the system is in a locked-down state.

